{% block head %}
  {% set socialImage = socialImage %}
  {% include "partials/head-meta.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

<main class="main-content">
  <section class="content-container">

    <!-- ✦ Intro -->
    <h4 class="index-heading">
      Journeys through the world’s afterlife traditions: pages revealing death, rebirth,
      and the soul’s passage beyond the veil.
    </h4>

    <!-- ✦ Disclaimer -->
    <details class="disclaimer-box">
      <summary>
        <span class="disclaimer-heading">☥ About the Afterlife Series</span>
      </summary>

      <p>
        <strong>The Afterlife Series</strong> explores the sacred maps of death and return preserved
        in the world’s great mystical traditions. Each page follows the soul’s movement through
        judgement, transformation, remembrance, and ascent.
      </p>

      <p>
        From the Gnostic revelations of early Christianity to the contemplative paths of Sufi Islam,
        the luminous ascent of Kabbalah, the bardos of Buddhism, the resurrection science of Ancient
        Egypt and the calendrical cosmologies of Mesoamerica, these teachings show that death is not
        a cessation but a passage. A return to the Source from which all spirits arise.
      </p>
    </details>

    <!-- ✦ Grid -->
    {% include "partials/pillar-grid.njk" %}

    <!-- ✦ JSON-LD Collection -->
    {% set items = pillarGrid %}
    {% set headline = "The Afterlife — Series Collections" %}
    {% set base = "/pillars/the-teachings/the-great-return/the-afterlife/" %}
    {% include "partials/jsonld-collection.njk" %}

    <!-- ✦ Divider -->
    <div class="gnostic-divider">
      <span class="divider-symbol pillar-glyph spin glow" aria-hidden="true">
        {{ glyph }}
      </span>
    </div>

  </section>
</main>